      "amount": "4-6, minced"
    },
    {
      "name": "Salt and Pepper",
      "notes": "to taste"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add onions and garlic to the heated oil and cook until translucent.",
    "Stir in halved tomatoes along with bay leaves, thyme sprigs, salt, and pepper. Cook for about 10 minutes stirring occasionally.",
    "Reduce heat to low-medium and simmer for another 5-7 minutes or until sauce thickens slightly.",
    "Serve warm as a side dish or over bread for an authentic Algerian breakfast experience."
